The paper deals with fundamental limits on estimation accuracy and optimal non-adaptive procedures, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the Berry-Esseen theorem suggests a focus on probability and statistics (cs.DS), while the consideration of adaptive query procedures suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
